}\n|goals2 =Gordon {{goal|29}}\n|stadium =[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =3,000\n|referee =F Scott\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==League Cup==\n{{Main|1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup}}\nThe League Cup saw Dumbarton again struggle to progress from their section, finishing 3rd of 4, with just 2 wins and a draw from their 6 games.\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = D\n|date =9 August 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Group 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 5\u20135\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[Stenhousemuir F.C.|Stenhousemuir]]\n|goals1 =Ross {{goal|20|pen}}<br>Goldie {{goal|23}}<br>Cantwell {{goal|34||84}}<br>Bootland {{goal|58}}\n|goals2 =McFarlane {{goal|30}}<br>Napier {{goal|52}}<br>Hope {{goal|53||55}}<br>McCormack {{goal|88}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =4,500\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =16 August 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Group 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 1\u20133\n|team1 =[[Arbroath F.C.|Arbroath]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Hill {{goal|35}}\n|goals2 =Morrison {{goal|8||57}}<br>Shields {{goal|27}}\n|stadium=[[Gayfield Park]]\n|attendance =4,000\n|referee =J B Smillie\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =23 August 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Group 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 1\u20130\n|team1 =[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Irving {{goal|33}}\n|goals2 =\n|stadium=[[Muirton Park]]\n|attendance =7,500\n|referee =J Jackson\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =30 August 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Group 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 2\u20131\n|team1 =[[Stenhousemuir F.C.|Stenhousemuir]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Bow {{goal|13||16}}\n|goals2 =Goldie {{goal|38}}\n|stadium=[[Ochilview]]\n|attendance =2,000\n|referee =W Davidson\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =6 September 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Group 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 4\u20132\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[Arbroath F.C.|Arbroath]]\n|goals1 =Donegan {{goal|8}}<br>Cantwell {{goal|30||60|pen|83}}\n|goals2 =Esplin {{goal|57}}<br>Carrie {{goal|62}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =2,500\n|referee =R G Benzie\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =13 September 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Group 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 1\u20136\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]\n|goals1 =Cantwell {{goal|79}}\n|goals2 =Brown {{goal|15||31||50}}<br>Goldie {{goal|44}}<br>Smeaton {{goal|80}}<br>McGowan {{goal|84}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =4,000\n|referee =W G Livingston\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Scottish Cup==\n{{Main|1947\u201348 Scottish Cup}}\nAfter negotiating a tricky trip to the Highlands, Dumbarton were defeated by high flying Division B opponents East Fife in the third round.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =7 February 1948\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish Cup#Second round|Round 2]]\n|score = 1\u20132\n|team1 =[[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Johnstone,B {{goal|11}}\n|goals2 =Goldie {{goal|31||41}}\n|stadium=[[Balmoor Stadium]]\n|attendance =5,473\n|referee =A Mowat\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =21 February 1948\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish Cup#Third round|Round 3]]\n|score = 0\u20131\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]]\n|goals1 =\n|goals2 =Davidson,J {{goal|79}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =8,000\n|referee =J Jackson\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==[[B Division Supplementary Cup|Supplementary Cup]]==\nAs in the Scottish Cup, Dumbarton again came up against East Fife and the outcome was the same, with the Fifers progressing to the semi final.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =7 January 1948\n|