ackson\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =30 August 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Section 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 2\u20131\n|team1 =[[Stenhousemuir F.C.|Stenhousemuir]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Bow {{goal|13||16}}\n|goals2 =Goldie {{goal|38}}\n|stadium=[[Ochilview]]\n|attendance =2,000\n|referee =W Davidson\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =6 September 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Section 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 4\u20132\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[Arbroath F.C.|Arbroath]]\n|goals1 =Donegan {{goal|8}}<br>Cantwell {{goal|30||60|pen|83}}\n|goals2 =Esplin {{goal|57}}<br>Carrie {{goal|62}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =2,500\n|referee =R G Benzie\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =13 September 1947\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup#Section 7|Section 7]]\n|score = 1\u20136\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]\n|goals1 =Cantwell {{goal|79}}\n|goals2 =Brown {{goal|15||31||50}}<br>Goldie {{goal|44}}<br>Smeaton {{goal|80}}<br>McGowan {{goal|84}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =4,000\n|referee =W G Livingston\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Scottish Cup==\n{{Main|1947\u201348 Scottish Cup}}\nAfter negotiating a tricky trip to the Highlands, Dumbarton were defeated by high flying Division B opponents East Fife in the third round.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =7 February 1948\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish Cup#Second round|Round 2]]\n|score = 1\u20132\n|team1 =[[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Johnstone,B {{goal|11}}\n|goals2 =Goldie {{goal|31||41}}\n|stadium=[[Balmoor Stadium]]\n|attendance =5,473\n|referee =A Mowat\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =21 February 1948\n|round =[[1947\u201348 Scottish Cup#Third round|Round 3]]\n|score = 0\u20131\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]]\n|goals1 =\n|goals2 =Davidson,J {{goal|79}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =8,000\n|referee =J Jackson\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==[[B Division Supplementary Cup|Supplementary Cup]]==\nAs in the Scottish Cup, Dumbarton again came up against East Fife and the outcome was the same, with the Fifers progressing to the semi final.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =7 January 1948\n|round =Round 1\n|score = 3\u20132\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[Stenhousemuir F.C.|Stenhousemuir]]\n|goals1 =McCreadie {{goal|}}<br>Goldie {{goal|}}<br>Wardlaw {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =Hope {{goal|}}{{goal|}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =12 April 1948\n|round =Round 2\n|score = 2\u20130\n|team1 =[[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 = {{goal|}} {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =\n|stadium=[[Bayview Stadium]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==[[Stirlingshire Cup]]==\nDumbarton lost out to Division A Falkirk in the semi final.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =21 August 1947\n|round =Round 1\n|score = 2\u20131\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[East Stirlingshire F.C.|East Stirlingshire]]\n|goals1 =Donegan {{goal|5}}<br>Ross {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =Cunningham {{goal|}}\n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =1,500\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =19 April 1948\n|round =Semi Final\n|score = 3\u20132\n|team2 =[[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]]\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Inglis {{goal|10||42||44}}\n|goals2 =Wardlaw {{goal|5}}<br>Goldie {{goal|40}}\n|stadium=[[Brockville Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =J R Boyd\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Benefit Match==\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =10 September 1946\n|round =[[Benefit Match|Benefit]]\n|score = 5\u20133\n|team1 =[[Airdrieonians F.C. (1878)|Airdrie]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 ={{goal|}} {{goal|}} {{goal|}} {{goal|}} {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =Cantwell {{goal|}}<br>Docherty {{goal|}}<br>Wagstaffe {{goal|}}\n|stadium=[[Millburn Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Player statistics==\n=== Squad<ref>{{cite book | last = McAllister | first = Jim | title = The Sons of the Rock - The Official History of Dumbarton Football Club | publisher = J&J Robertson Printers | year = 2002 | location = Dumbarton}}</ref> ===\n{{Efs start|[[1947\u201348 Scottish Division Two|B Division]]|[[1947\u201348 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]]|[[1947\u201348 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]]|[[B Division Supplementary Cup|Supplementary Cup]]}}\n{{Efs player|name=Finlayson|pos=GK|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Jim Hoey|pos=GK|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|3|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Archie McFeat]]|pos=GK|nat=SCO|7|0|1|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Stan Gullan]]|pos=GK|nat=SCO|10|0|0|0|3|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Ian Ogilvie]]|pos=GK|nat=SCO|11|0|1|0|0|0|2|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Alex Kay|pos=DF|nat=SCO|2|0|0|0|0|0|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Jack McNee (footballer 1950's)|Jack McNee]]|pos=DF|nat=SCO|19|0|2|0|6|0|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Jimmy Michie|pos=DF|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Jimmy Mulvaney]]|pos=DF|nat=SCO|28|0|2|0|6|0|2|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Thomas Ashe (footballer)|Thomas Ashe]]|pos=MF|nat=SCO|26|3|2|0|3|0|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[George Campbell (footballer, born 1920)|George Campbell]]|pos=MF|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|2|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Bobby Donaldson (footballer)|Bobby Donaldson]]|pos=MF|nat=SCO|22|0|2|0|6|0|2|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Ian Hepburn|pos=MF|nat=SCO|7|0|0|0|0|0|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=John Kelly|pos=MF|nat=SCO|2|0|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Lawrie Lindsay]]|pos=MF|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|2|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Gordon McFarlane|pos=MF|nat=SCO|2|0|0|0|2|0|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Alex Menzies]]|pos=MF|nat=SCO|21|0|0|0|0|0|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Bobby Ross (footballer, born 1917)|Bobby Ross]]|pos=MF|nat=SCO|26|1|2|0|3|1|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Charles Bootland|Charlie Bootland]]|pos=FW|nat=SCO|21|9|2|0|6|1|1|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Bobby Caldwell|pos=FW|nat=SCO|5|3|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Jackie Cantwell]]|pos=FW|nat=SCO|26|10|0|0|3|6|2|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Hugh Docherty|pos=FW|nat=SCO|0|0|0|0|1|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Tom Donegan]]|pos=FW|nat=SCO|28|8|2|0|6|1|2|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Hugh Goldie (footballer, born 1923)|Hugh Goldie]]|pos=FW|nat=SCO|29|10|2|2|6|2|2|1}}\n{{Efs player|name=Peter Grant|pos=FW|nat=SCO|1|2|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Eddie McCreadie|pos=FW|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|0|0|1|1}}\n{{Efs player|name=Neil McLean|pos=FW|nat=SCO|5|2|2|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=John McLennan|pos=FW|nat=SCO|3|4|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Dave Morrison|pos=FW|nat=SCO|2|1|0|0|4|2|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Jimmy Shields|pos=FW|nat=SCO|2|1|0|0|2|1|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Jimmy Smith (footballer, born 1902)|Jimmy Smith]]|pos=FW|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|2|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Edwin Wagstaffe|pos=FW|nat=SCO|1|0|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Johh Wardlaw|pos=FW|nat=SCO|17|13|2|0|0|0|1|1}}\n|}\n\n===Transfers===\nAmongst those players joining and leaving the club were the following:<ref>{{cite book | last = Litster | first = John | title = Record of Post-War Scottish League Players | publisher = PM Publications | location = Norwich}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n==== Players in ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%;width:98%; text-align:left\"\n|-\n!Player\n!From\n!Date\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jackie Cantwell]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n| 9 Jun 1947\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Hugh Goldie (footballer, born 1923)|Hugh Goldie]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Armadale Thistle F.C.|Armadale Thistle]] \n| 7 Jul 1947\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jack McNee (footballer 1950's)|Jack McNee]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Carluke Rovers F.C.|Carluke Rovers]] \n| 4 Aug 1947\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n==== Players out ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%;width:98%; text-align:left\"\n|-\n!Player\n!To\n!Date\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Jimmy Timmins\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton]]\n| 18 Aug 1947\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Jim Hoey\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Stirling Albion F.C.|Stirling Alb]]\n| 7 Oct 1947\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Thomas Ashe (footballer)|Thomas Ashe]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Freed\n| 30 Apr 1948\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Reserve team==\nDumbarton entered the Scottish Second XI Cup but lost in the first round to Ayr United.\n\n==Trivia==\n* The number of goals conceded in all games during the season was 111, the 12th time the unwanted 'century' had been broken.\n\n==See also==\n* [[1947\u201348 in Scottish football]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=5853 Finlayson (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=377 Jim Hoey (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=601 Alex Kay (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=5852 Jimmy Michie (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=522 Ian Hepburn (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=597 John Kelly (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=614 Gordon McFarlane (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=5854 Bobby Caldwell (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=590 Hugh Docherty (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=606 Peter Grant (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=595 Eddie McCreadie (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*